Continuous Deployment in 3 hours
================================

This is the accompanying material for the workshop Continuous Deployment in
3 hours by Mike van Riel.

Requirements
------------

To be able to follow this workshop you will need to have the following software packages installed:

* [git](http://git-scm.com)
* [Vagrant](http://www.vagrantup.com)
* [Virtualbox](http://www.virtualbox.com)

Setting up your environment
---------------------------

1. clone this repository:

      git clone [x]

2. Setup and install submodules:

      git submodule update --init --recursive

3. Setup the development environment using Vagrant

  1. When using a base-box provided at the workshop:

    1. copy the base-box to location x
    2. Change the Vagrantfile's config.vm.box and config.vm.box_url entry to match the location of your base-box

  2. Run `vagrant up`

4. Add the following line to your hosts file:

    192.168.42.42 dev.my.blog.com

5. Profit $$$ !

After the above you can go to http://dev.www.blog.com/index.php/blog/ to see the result of your work.
